Very few writefags here snowflake their protaganons (with durr being an exception). No story lionizes humanity specifically for anything; that's just thread chatter. The protagonists are human because that's this thread's theme. In many stories, if the anthropomorphic love interest isn't attracted to Anon solely for his character, the catalysts that initiate his courtship with a story's principal waifur are usually social taboos, a flaw in the waifur's character by which she is attracted to him (eg, human fetishism). To be honest, and I qualify the following as critique, in many stories, writefags work so hard to ground their protaganons and make their stories believable, that the characters themselves are intentionally written as total losers. I personally enjoy zero-to-Aristotelian good life stories, but it places too much work on the principal waifur, more than anybody would realistically pursue; "Anon Finds a Way" comes to mind as being subverted by this trope (despite that flaw, and Shark's expository tendency to tell over showing, I love that story). Going back to /hmofa/'s basics though, "Ruth the Bat" does a great job of making that relationship flow organically, without denigrating Ruth or Anon in any way that's more than light comedy.
